                <p><b>Solved Problem: </b>Digoxin is available in a concentration of 0.1 mg/ml. How many ml would provide a dose of 1.5 mg?</p>
                <p><b>Approach: </b></p>             
                <div class="formulae"><p>$${0.1(mg) \over 1.5(mg)} = {1(ml) \over x(ml)} $$ </p></div>
                <div class="formulae"><p>$${x(ml)} = { {1.5(mg) \times 1(ml)} \over 0.1(ml)} $$</p></div>
                <p><b>Answer: </b>  15 ml </p>
