                <p><i>Inverse Proportions</i> equate two products. One example important to pharmaceutical calculations involves dilution of solutions. 
                The product of volume times concentration (= amount) stays the same and thus the new concentration after dilution can be calculated. </p>    
                <div ><p >$${Concentration_1 \times Volume_1} = Concentration_2 \times Volume_2 $$</p></div>
                
